<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880114-0046 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Bairnco Corp. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> BZ </CO><TEXT>   Bairnco Corp., New York, expects to report that fourth-quarter net income increased 7% on a 5% rise in sales.    The maker of lighting products, electronic parts and other items had profit in the year-earlier quarter of $7.7 million, or 75 cents a share, on sales of $154.3 million.    Bairnco said full-year profit rose 24% to about $28 million, or more than $2.65 a share, from $22.5 million, or $2.20 a share in 1986. Sales grew about 8% to $629 million from $585.1 million.    Bairnco said more than half of its 1987 sales gain came from growth in continuing operations with the balance attributable to acquisitions.    In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday, Bairnco was unchanged at $26.875 a share. </TEXT></DOC>